en:
We're in the final stages of the assault on the enemy base.

We have the enemy right where we want them -- a small valley within range of our artillery.
es:
Estamos en las etapas finales del asalto a la base enemiga.

Tenemos al enemigo justo donde queremos: un pequeño valle al alcance de nuestra artillería.

en:
We'll begin firing rocket artillery and need you to scout out the enemy position to confirm their destruction.

Your job will be to clean up any targets that remain after the artillery barrage.
es:
Comenzaremos a disparar la artillería de cohetes y necesitamos que reconozcas la posición enemiga para confirmar su destrucción.

Tu misión será eliminar cualquier objetivo que quede después del bombardeo de artillería.

en: Once the main enemy battalion has been destroyed, we'll have you scout out and destroy a few other secondary targets to support our ground forces and clear the way for our bombers.
es: Una vez destruido el batallón enemigo principal, te haremos reconocer y destruir algunos objetivos secundarios para apoyar a nuestras fuerzas terrestres y despejar el camino para nuestros bombarderos.

en: Your role is crucial in this final push towards victory. Good luck!
es: Tu papel es crucial en este empuje final hacia la victoria. ¡Buena suerte!

en: Practice taking off and landing in various locations.
es: Practica despegues y aterrizajes en varios lugares.

en: Just follow each waypoint. Can you make each landing smoother or more efficient than the last?
es: Simplemente siga cada punto. ¿Puede hacer que cada aterrizaje sea más suave o más eficiente que el anterior?

en: Finish the mission by landing on the moving cruiser's deck.
es: Termina la misión aterrizando en la cubierta del crucero en movimiento.

en:
Welcome!

I know you've been itching for a bit of action so I have a few tasks lined up for you today.

Let's get started.
es:
¡Bienvenido!

Sé que has estado deseando un poco de acción, así que tengo algunas tareas preparadas para ti hoy.

Empecemos.

en:
A huge mountain range divides us from the enemy territory, so we usually don't get too much activity in the area.

Recently we began spotting small groups passing through and setting up small camps on our side of the ridge.
es:
Una enorme cadena montañosa nos separa del territorio enemigo, así que normalmente no hay mucha actividad en la zona.

Recientemente hemos empezado a detectar pequeños grupos que cruzan y montan pequeños campamentos en nuestro lado de la cresta.









Preguntar a ChatGPT

en:
They appear to be setting up forward operating bases to service their VTOL capable attack aircraft.

They are still early in the preparation stage so we should attack now before they get too fortified.
es:
Parece que están estableciendo bases de operaciones avanzadas para dar servicio a sus aeronaves de ataque con capacidad VTOL.

Aún están en una etapa temprana de preparación, así que deberíamos atacar ahora antes de que se fortifiquen demasiado.

en:
We currently have positive intel on two camps.  We know where they are, and that they're only equipped with small arms, so this should be a breeze for you.

Their locations are available in the objective data.
es:
Actualmente tenemos información confirmada sobre dos campamentos. Sabemos dónde están y que solo están equipados con armas ligeras, así que esto debería ser pan comido para ti.

Sus ubicaciones están disponibles en los datos del objetivo.

en:
After you clear out those sites, there will be one more matter we need to look into.  

We are aware of transport activity in the high mountain region so we'll have you go and perform some recon.  Be sure to bring enough fuel.
es:
Después de despejar esos sitios, habrá un asunto más que necesitamos investigar.

Tenemos conocimiento de actividad de transporte en la región montañosa alta, así que te enviaremos a realizar una misión de reconocimiento. Asegúrate de llevar suficiente combustible.

en:
Absolutely never go beyond the mountain range and into the plains.

Beyond that point is the enemy territory which is heavily defended by long range air defenses and fighters.

Summary
 Objectives
 - Destroy all targets at sites A and B
 - Perform recon in the high mountains
 Threats
 - Small arms fire
- MANPADS

For this mission, you will need to act quickly and quietly.

The enemy plans to launch several groups of aircraft from their base.

Your objective is to destroy all of these aircraft before they take off.

You will be taking off from a forward arming and refueling point (FARP) about 30 miles from the target.

Fly low and make your way to the to the airbase undetected.

A bomber is inbound to land at the airbase.  After it lands, the enemy fighters will begin to take off.  

You will have this window to strike while all aircraft are still on the ground.
Beware that if they spot you before you are ready to attack, they may launch preemptively to defend themselves.

SUMMARY

Primary Targets:
- Landed aircraft

Threats:
- IR guided SAMs
- Small arms fire
- AAA

Practice using the AH-94's weapons on various targets.

Targets will not shoot back so take your time to learn the equipment.

Check the objectives data to find targets.
Learn how to use air-to-ground missiles.
Destroy some of the targets around the waypoint using the AGM-114.
Learn how to use the cannon, rockets, and targeting system.
Learn how to use the hover autopilot feature.
Today, you will learn how to use air-to-ground missiles (AGMs) to destroy armored ground targets.
Learn how to use the virtual flight controls to taxi, take off, and land the AV-42C "Kestrel".

Today we will be learning how to operate the AV-42C.

The start-up procedure is not very complicated, so let's jump in and get started.

The AV-42C is capable of equipping various weapons.  Today you will learn how to use the 30mm GAU-8 cannon, and the Hydra-70 unguided rockets.  You will also learn how to find and acquire targets using the TGP.
Vertical flight can be tricky, but by using the hover autopilot, you can take off, hover, and land with ease.
Learn how to use the radar to find, track, and lock onto aircraft.
Shoot the target with an AIM-120
Learn how to use the ARAD and AGM-88 to destroy radar targets.
The F/A-26B is equipped with powerful forward facing radar. Learn how to use it to detect and track other aircraft.  Lock onto enemy targets to allow you to fire radar guided missiles.

One of the most abundant and dangerous threats to aircraft are Surface-to-Air Missiles (SAMs), most of which rely on radar to find and track targets.

Suppression of Enemy Air Defense (SEAD) operations neutralize or destroy these threats.

One method of performing SEAD involves destroying the radar used by the SAMs.

You will learn how to use the Anti-Radar Attack Display (ARAD) in conjunction with the AGM-88 weapon to locate, target, and destroy enemy radars.
Introduction to the vehicle, and a general overview of the cockpit.
How to start up and shut down the AH-94.
Control the TADS with the TEDAC and use it to slave the gun.
Learn about the AH-94 and take a quick look at each of the components in the cockpit.
Learn the steps to properly start up the engines, spin up the rotor, and safely turn everything off.
Learn about the TADS, controlling it with the TEDAC, and steering the gun turret.
A collection of cooperative or freeflight scenarios for multiplayer.
Use cooperation and the advanced capabilities of the F-45A to complete various objectives.
Destroy bunkers and supply tents at enemy airbase.
Destroy the enemy unit on the way to attack our base.
Destroy the MAD-4 set up near base to allow our AWACS to deploy.
Fly strike missions off the Aircraft Carrier with your buddies.
Destroy the enemy's secret bunkers hidden in the caldera.
Destroy the mine laying ships parked in the bay.
Find and destroy all ships in the enemy carrier group.
Find and kill the enemy leadership hiding in the town.
Do not allow your carrier to be destroyed.

Your team of F-45 pilots have been tasked to carry out an attack against the enemy.

Use cooperation and the advanced capabilities of your aircraft to complete the mission.

The first objective is to destroy the enemy Mobile Air Defense units (MAD-4) which are stationed just outside of our airbase.

We can't deploy our AWACS until these air defenses are eliminated.

A convoy of tanks are on their way to our base.  They may be little more than a nuisance to you, but destroy them nonetheless.  If they reach the base they will likely start destroying our supplies and other assets.
At your discretion, complete the rest of the mission by finding and destroying the numerous hostile aircraft, and finally busting the bunkers and supply depots at the enemy base.

This is a freeflight scenario with no objectives.

A

The carrier strike group has arrived at the enemy's doorstep in the northern sea.

Launch with your wingmen and take on the various objectives.

The skies are covered by enemy patrols and air defense units.  

Split the responsibilities of CAP, SEAD and Attack among your team members and work together to complete the mission.
Each team gets 4x F/A-26Bs and 2x F-45As. First team to 24 points wins!
Quick dogfight match for F/A-26B with guns and heat seeking missiles (AIM-9). First team to 24 points wins!
6 vs 6 Kestrels!  This was originally to look for bugs relating to the AV-42C.
Rescue your soldiers from the enemy base and bring them back to your own. Each team will need to bring home 3 soldiers.
Bring the final soldier to homeplate!
Quick dogfight match for F/A-26B. First team to 24 points wins!
Destroy the ground targets at the enemy base before they destroy yours. Defend your own assets from the enemy attack.
Destroy bunkers and supply tents at the enemy airbase.
Destroy tents and bunkers at Outpost A.
Destroy tents and bunkers at Outpost B.
Destroy the ground targets at the enemy base before they destroy yours. Defend your own assets from the enemy attack. Low-tech weapons only.
Destroy bunkers and supply tents at the enemy airbase.
Destroy tents and bunkers at Outpost A.
Destroy tents and bunkers at Outpost B.
Each team gets 4x F/A-26Bs and 2x F-45As. Try out some pure air combat!
The bases are about 75 nautical miles apart, so you will be able to spread out and make use of BVR (beyond visual range) tactics.
The first team to score 24 kills wins.
You're in the merge!  Get ready for a fight!
Use your guns, missiles, and flares to achieve victory!
This is just a test scenario for the AV-42C.

The object of the game is to pick up and bring home 3 soldiers.

You will need at least one AV-42C on your team to complete the objectives.

Only one soldier will appear at a time.  Once you successfully bring home the soldier, a new one will appear in a different location.

Each new soldier will be closer to the enemy base.
The soldiers can't be killed.  If an AV-42C is shot down while carrying a soldier, the soldier will return to its spawn point.

This is a classic guns-only dogfight scenario. 

You will spawn head to head with your opponents.  

Prepare for combat!
Try to avoid shooting before the merge!
The first team to suffer 24 deaths loses.

In this scenario, each team has assets that they will need to defend, as well as enemy targets they need to destroy.

Work together with your team to attack and defend.

Team A is based in the north-western region, while Team B is in the south-eastern region.

Each team has 3 outposts which are the primary targets to attack/defend.

Work together with your team to attack and defend.

Team A is based in the north-western region, while Team B is in the south-eastern region.

Each team has 3 outposts which are the primary targets to attack/defend.

Spearhead the effort to liberate a city under enemy occupation.
Destroy or disable all MAD-4 units.
Disable the long range air defenses on the ships.
Find the makeshift HQ and destroy all of its major assets.
Destroy patrolling GAV-25 group, or let our fighters handle it.
Escort special forces unit Bravo to extract the civillians.
Destroy the armored units moving up the road towards our base.
Destroy the 3 APCs carrying the enemy dictators.
Find and destroy rocket artillery trucks.

The city has been overrun by the enemy. They've taken complete control and have set up a makeshift HQ at the city center.

Most of the civillians have been evacuated, however a small group is trapped in one of the industrial buildings.
Our main goal today is to get those civillians to safety, but there are a few steps we need to take in order to do that.

A pair enemy ground attack aircraft are patrolling the area.  They need to be destroyed before we can begin the rescue operation.

We would send in fighters to take care of them but the enemy have strong air defenses.

This is where you will begin.

Destroy the MAD-4 units around the city, as well as the long range anti-air missile systems on the ships parked off the coast.

This will allow us to send the fighters to gain air superiority.

Once the air defenses and air patrol are destroyed, special forces unit Bravo will enter the city by road vehicles.

You will need to provide close air support and clear their way through the city streets.

Finally, while we have you on station and are maintaining air superiority, we need you to find the HQ that the enemy has set up downtown.  They are storing valuable supplies and equipment there, so destroy everything you find.

SUMMARY
Objectives
1. SEAD (MAD-4 and ship SAMs)
 2. Destroy enemy aircraft (with help)
 3. Escort Bravo on rescue mission
 4. Find and destroy assets at enemy HQ
Threats
- SAMs, infantry, attack aircraft

Tonight, we're taking on a daring but crucial mission.

It's time to stop enemy's reign of terror.

We'll be launching from the carrier at midnight.
The enemy leaders have been highly elusive, but thanks to our network of informants, we have intel that all of the top officials will be in Pike City to oversee an inspection of 5 new warships.

The city, and the harbor especially, are heavily defended, but we can't pass up this opportunity.

Move towards the harbor, delaying detection as long as possible.  The moment they know we're here, the leaders will attempt to flee the city.
The primary objective is to assassinate the leaders, who will be riding in 3 armored personnel carriers (APCs).
We are also aware that mobile artillery units, both land and sea, are ready to deploy when provoked, so we must find them and destroy them before they can fire on our ships.
Find and assassinate the leaders, destroy the artillery boats and trucks, then return to the carrier.

en: Welcome to the air-to-ground missile tutorial!
Air-to-ground missiles (AGM) are useful for precisely hitting light to medium armored ground targets
You will use the TGP to designate targets for the AGMs
These are small, laser-guided, anti-tank missiles
Since they home in on the laser point emitted by your TGP, you must maintain line of sight to the target until it hits
To fire it, designate a target using the TGP, point your aircraft at the target until the missile locks on, then pull the trigger to fire
You can also switch the missile seeker's uncage mode to MANUAL, which will allow you to fire at targets off boresight
In MANUAL mode, you hold the trigger to uncage the seeker, then press the weapon switch button to fire
Try shooting the targets around the mission waypoint using the AGM-114
Remember, you need to maintain line of sight with your TGP in order to guide the missile to the target
Great! Now switch to the AGM-65
This is a larger, slightly heavier hitting anti-tank missile with a more advanced optical seeker
With this type of missile, you do not need to maintain a lock on the target after you fire at it
The fire-and-forget capability allows you to fire at multiple targets in one pass, or take cover after firing
Try taking down the targets at the next waypoint and practice taking advantage of the fire-and-forget capability
Nice shooting!  This concludes the air-to-ground missile tutorial
Welcome to the Radar tutorial for the F/A-26
Today, you will learn how to use the radar to find and track other aircraft, as well as designate targets for air to air missiles
The display shows you a compressed representation of the radar's 120 degree field of view
The displayed range can be adjusted using the R+ and R- buttons
Press R+ repeatedly until the display is at max range
As the radar sweeps over other aircraft, they will be displayed as blue icons for friends and orange icons for foes
The left/right SCAN ANGLE can also be adjusted to allow the radar to scan more rapidly but in a smaller slice of the sky
Now, you can slew the target designator using the joystick's thumb control
Slew the designator over a contact, and press in on the center of the thumb control to start tracking it
You can track up to 4 contacts while still being able to scan the rest of the sky
They will appear as small circle on your HUD, along with their corresponding number
In order to lock a target for weapons, click on a track again using the designator, or press the numbered MFD button on the left
While a target is locked, the other tracks will continue to be displayed, but the radar will not be able to scan for new targets
Information about the locked target's bearing, range, altitude, airspeed, and aircraft type will appear on the bottom right of the display
Use the UNLCK button to unlock the target, and the CLR button to clear the tracks
For close in engagements, the radar can be switched to boresight mode using the MODE button
In this mode, the radar will point straight forward and lock onto the first contact it sees
If the radar is SOI, you can press the joystick thumb control to quickly unlock and find a new target
Now for some weapons practice. Go back to scan mode and find, track, and lock the enemy aircraft.
Good. Now arm your weapon system and switch to the AIM-120
On the HUD, the locked target will appear as a small square.  The small dot is the shot lead cue
When firing air to air missiles, aim for the lead cue to help the missile conserve energy as it steers toward the target
The DLZ is displayed on the right side of the HUD. The missile should be fired when the target chevron lies between the min and max marks
By tracking multiple contacts, you can fire up to 4 AIM-120s on separate targets as long as you maintain line of sight with each of them
When the AIM-120's time to impact counter displays the letter M, it has switched to active homing and you no longer need to track it.
Now, try shooting down the rest of the enemy air targets.
Out of missiles!  You hit some of the targets though!
Out of missiles!  You didn't hit anything.  Want to try again?
SEAD stands for Suppression of Enemy Air Defenses
You will use a combination of radar detecting sensors and special weapons to disable SAM sites
When a radar is searching for aircraft, it emits a signal that can be detected by your RWR
The radar type, bearing, and approximate range is shown on the RWR display, relative to your position in the center
This display shows the same information gathered by the RWR, but allows you to select targets for ARMs
You can also set radar sources to be displayed as diamonds in the HUD
When you lower the AR visor, you'll be able to see all of the targets around you for better situational awareness
Now you can use your joystick thumb control to slew the targeting cursor
Slew the cursor onto the enemy radar, then press in on the thumb control to set the target
A square will appear on the selected target in both the MFD and the HUD
This is a high speed, fire-and-forget anti-radiation missile (ARM)
